veral locations in the Midwest and a few locations in the Southern Great Plains and in Montana also show losses of 20 million or more. Most other counties show losses of 1 million or less or 1 to 10 million. Areas with heavy losses in 2020 also tend to show the largest increases in losses for 2050, generally in the 10 to 20 percent or 20 percent or more ranges. However, many counties in the Midwest, Northern and Southern Great Plains, and Southwest do show decreases</aside>
